    - name: Component Structure
      rule: |
        Follow these patterns for component implementation:
        - Use functional components with hooks, not class components
        - Implement TypeScript interfaces for component props
        - Use the forwardRef pattern for components that need ref 
  forwarding
        - Follow the established component structure:
          - Import statements grouped by type
          - Component props interface
          - useState/useRef declarations
          - useEffect/useLayoutEffect hooks for side effects
          - Conditional rendering functions
          - Main JSX return
        - Use the VS component wrappers for theme-aware styling:
          - VSBackground, VSCard, VSSection for containers
          - VSText, VSHeading, VSGradientText for text
          - VSButton, VSIconButton for buttons